   "body" : "https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/BIP_0037 states that \"version\" P2P message is extended by one byte.  bitcoind's code appears to read this,\r\n```\r\n        if (!vRecv.empty())\r\n            vRecv >> pfrom->fRelayTxes; // set to true after we get the first fi\r\nlter* message\r\n        else\r\n            pfrom->fRelayTxes = true;\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut does not appear to send the fRelayTxes byte:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    PushMessage(\"version\", PROTOCOL_VERSION, nLocalServices, nTime, addrYou, addrMe,\r\n                nLocalHostNonce, FormatSubVersion(CLIENT_NAME, CLIENT_VERSION, std::vector<string>()), nBestHeight);\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
